The decibels command, db, reports data on all or part of an audio file,
both monaural and stereo.  The command may be qualified by one or a
comma separated pair of initial addresses to limit the portion of the
file to be reported.  The user is shown the sound level, the maximum
excursions in the negative and positive directions, and the value of a
possible DC component.  Separate values for left and right channels are
not reported, use the cs command for that purpose.  To report the entire
file, use one of these equivalent forms: ",db" or "1,$db".  The db command
can also be used to modify the sound level of a file.  Type db, a space,
and the decibel level or RMS value desired.  Values between -60 and +20
are taken as decibel levels, values above +20 are taken as RMS values.
The initial address or address range may be used when modifying loudness,
as well as when reporting it.

